extends layout

block body
  #hero
    #progressBar
    #statusTop
      span.show-leech #{ 'Downloading ' }
      span.show-seed #{ 'Seeding ' }
      code: a#torrentLink(href='https://webtorrent.io/torrents/sintel.torrent') sintel.torrent
      span.show-leech #{ ' from ' }
      span.show-seed #{ ' to ' }
      code#numPeers 0 peers
      | #{ '. ' }
    #statusBottom
      code#downloaded
      | #{ ' of '}
      code#total
      | #{ ' — '}
      span#remaining
    #svgWrap
    #videoWrap
      .video

  .feature-block
    article
      h1.beta-release Introducing WebTorrent Desktop
      a(href='/desktop', title='WebTorrent Desktop')
        img(src='/img/screenshot-player.png')
      h2 The streaming torrent client for OS X, Window, and Linux
      p WebTorrent Desktop is fast, free, totally non-commercial and open source. WebTorrent Desktop can talk to both BitTorrent and WebTorrent peers.
      div.featuredCenter
        a.btn.large(href='/desktop') Check It Out

  .feature-block
    article
      :markdown
        # BitTorrent over WebRTC

        **WebTorrent** is a streaming torrent client for the **browser**. YEP, THAT'S RIGHT. THE BROWSER.

        It's written completely in JavaScript – the language of the web – and uses
        **WebRTC** for true peer-to-peer transport. No browser plugins, extensions, or
        installation is required.

        ## Why?

        Imagine a peer-to-peer YouTube where viewers help to host the site's content. By making BitTorrent easier to use, we can get more people to participate and take the first steps to re-decentralizing the Internet.

        ## How do I try it out?

        You can see WebTorrent in action at [Instant.io](https://instant.io).
        Send a file to a friend using BitTorrent!

  .feature-block
    article
      h1 Learn more about WebTorrent
      div.featuredCenter
        a.btn.large(href='/intro') Get Started
        a.btn.large(href='/docs') Docs
        a.btn.large(href='/faq') FAQ
